dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Theron b Langeveldt 78 (90b 4x4 1x6 118m) SR: 86.66

dismissalComment.html: oh dear. Taibu's gone! Or has he? Simple enough outside edge, went low to Theron at short third man who claimed the catch. The South African's were celebrating by Taibu hangs around. Eventually he's sent on his way and it ends an excellent innings.

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c †de Villiers b Theron 32 (39b 5x4 0x6 52m) SR: 82.05

dismissalComment.html: Theron strikes! Good change from Smith and it's the big wicket! Taylor defeated by a change of pace - he tried to hoik into the leg side but only managed a top edge that sailed behind him down to de Villiers who pouched it easily. Big breakthrough

dismissalComment.html: lovely, lovely slower one from Theron, cut away from outside leg stump, Dabengwa tried to work it on the on side, the bat face closed early, and the top edge balloons to the left of de Villiers who accepts his fourth catch of the innings gleefully

there's no need for the appeal this time, as another beautifully bowled slower one cleans up Cremer, it was short of a good length outside off and came back in ... ever so slowly ... to go past his cross-batted swipe and hit the top of off stump, and thats a fifer for Rusty, in only his second ODI, well done

commentTextItems.html: everyone knew what was going to happen, de Villiers was going to have a dart and he's sealed it in style, leaning back and smashing this into the stands behind the bowler's head. What a hundred! It only took 72 balls!

commentPostTextItems.html: South Africa win by eight wickets. Clinical work from South Africa, they were impressive with the ball - led by Rusty Theron's maiden five-for - before once again overpowering Zimbabwe with the bat. The home side take an unassailable 2-0 lead in the series. Rusty Theron is named on of the match for his 5 for 44 that set up the game.

Do check out Liam Brickhill's bulletin and if you're in the mood have a look at our Facebook page. Thanks for the emails, that will be all from us today, please join us on Friday for the final game of the series.

image.longCaption: Shingirai Masakadza portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

commentTextItems.html: full toss, pretty gentle stuff from Taylor, must be stiff from his marathon effort in the opening ODI, knocked down to long-off
drilled firmly back past the bowler to long-off
horrid ball, really dragged down and de Villiers didn't quite manage to punish it fully, swinging a pull down to deep square
de Villiers collects a couple whipping towards deep square

commentPreTextItems.html: Change in bowling here's Brendan Taylor.

commentTextItems.html: starts well enough, blocked carefully into the leg side
sliced off the outside edge down to long-off, Duminy was aiming midwicket

image.caption: Shingirai Masakadza
image.longCaption: Shingirai Masakadza portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

commentTextItems.html: dropped! By the captain as well! Duminy drove crisply straight to Chigumbura, but he spilled the chance
this time Duminy gets all of it, smashing a length ball through mid-on for a boundary
Duminy gets away with this, mistiming an expansive drive in the air over mid-on for a couple
not a great delivery this, bouncer down the leg side
another full ball, straight too, he's bowled well this spell, comes off bat into pad behind the stumps for a single
worked round the corner, more inside edge than middle, but a single nevertheless
more secure from Duminy here, pushed down the wicket

image.caption: Shingirai Masakadza
image.longCaption: Shingirai Masakadza portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

commentTextItems.html: Duminy is not nearly as fluent as yet and gets in a tangle as he comes down the wicket and has to defend
stroked towards cover for one
pushed into the legs side quietly this time
oh good shot again! de Villiers in a hurry! Skipping down the wicket and smacking this into the stands at long-on
lovely shot again, short enough for de Villiers to hop back and crash through point for four
good over in the end, Masakadza lands another yorker which is stabbed to long-on

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Theron b Langeveldt 78 (90b 4x4 1x6 118m) SR: 86.66

dismissalComment.html: oh dear. Taibu's gone! Or has he? Simple enough outside edge, went low to Theron at short third man who claimed the catch. The South African's were celebrating by Taibu hangs around. Eventually he's sent on his way and it ends an excellent innings.

dismissalText.commentary: Keith Dabengwa c †de Villiers b Theron 28 (23b 2x4 2x6 39m) SR: 121.73

dismissalComment.html: lovely, lovely slower one from Theron, cut away from outside leg stump, Dabengwa tried to work it on the on side, the bat face closed early, and the top edge balloons to the left of de Villiers who accepts his fourth catch of the innings gleefully

headshotImage.caption: Robin Peterson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Peterson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya c Peterson b Parnell 22 (18b 3x4 0x6 25m) SR: 122.22

dismissalComment.html: gone this time! hits this one on leg straight to the man at square leg, he wanted to go much squarer, but it came of the inside half of the bat, end of a breezy little knock from Utseya

headshotImage.caption: Rusty Theron player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Rusty Theron player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer b Theron 4 (4b 0x4 0x6 20m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: there's no need for the appeal this time, as another beautifully bowled slower one cleans up Cremer, it was short of a good length outside off and came back in ... ever so slowly ... to go past his cross-batted swipe and hit the top of off stump, and thats a fifer for Rusty, in only his second ODI, well done

image.caption: Shingirai Masakadza
image.longCaption: Shingirai Masakadza portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Hashim Amla c Utseya b Masakadza 110 (103b 12x4 0x6 128m) SR: 106.79

dismissalComment.html: gone this time though! Flicked powerfully straight to short midwicket. Ends another brilliant Amla knock
